item.title: Blood
item.description: Plasma mixture of water, sugar, fat, protein, and salts transport blood cells throughout your body along with nutrients, waste products, antibodies, clotting proteins, chemical messengers such as hormones. Red Blood Cells Aka erythrocytes or RBCs 40 to 45 percent of volume. Structure biconcave disk with a flattened center. like a donut no nucleus and so can easily change shape, helping them fit through the various blood vessels in your body.
